Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle to sharpish turn. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p..200, 35). Name Anaxiboulos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR P.15999.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1004)
